<TITLE> Archbishop's Christmas wish is for good polls </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 24 (bdnews24.com)  On the eve of elections in Bangladesh, the Archbishop of Dhaka urged all to be united in choosing good leaders for the country. "Let us unitedly choose the best leader for the country in the upcoming parliamentary election," said Archbishop Paulinus Costa in his Christmas Eve message to people of all faiths. "The teachings of Jesus Christ encapsulate love towards the poor and forgiveness." Churches throughout the capital were seen adorned with lights and Christmas decorations as celebrations began on the Eve, culminating in midnight mass to usher in Christmas Day. The main Christmas congregation was held at the Ramna Cathedral and conducted by Archbishop Costa THOUGH THE largest congregation of four to five thousand is traditionally seen at Tejgaon Church. President Iajuddin Ahmed and chief adviser Fakhruddin Ahmed issued separate messages on Christmas Eve. "We must always be alert in maintaining communal harmony in Bangladesh," said the chief adviser. AL president Sheikh Hasina and BNP chairperson Khaleda Zia also issued messages stressing religious tolerance and communal harmony. Sheikh Hasina said her party was pledge bound to safeguard the rights of all people irrespective of their faith, while Khaleda Zia noted that Bangladesh was a remarkable example of religious tolerance. bdnew
